---
import LegalPageLayout from "@layouts/LegalPageLayout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy";
const description =
  "This Privacy Policy explains what information Borys Online collects, how it is used, and what choices you have.";
const updatedAt = "March 30, 2026";
---

<LegalPageLayout title={title} description={description} updatedAt={updatedAt}>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy applies to the Borys Online website, related applications, and any services that link to this policy. By using our services, you agree to the collection and use of information as described below.
  </p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We may collect the following categories of information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Information you provide directly, such as emails or messages sent to us.</li>
    <li>Technical information such as browser type, device type, operating system, referring pages, and approximate usage data.</li>
    <li>Limited analytics or diagnostic information needed to operate, secure, and improve our services.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>We use collected information to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide, operate, maintain, and improve the website and applications.</li>
    <li>Respond to inquiries, support requests, and feedback.</li>
    <li>Monitor performance, prevent abuse, and protect the security of our services.</li>
    <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
  <p>
    We may use cookies or similar technologies for basic functionality, analytics, and remembering user preferences. You can control cookies through your browser settings, though disabling them may affect how some parts of the services function.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    We may rely on third-party providers for hosting, analytics, content delivery, or customer support. These providers may process information on our behalf under their own privacy terms and applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain personal information only for as long as reasonably necessary to provide the services, resolve disputes, maintain security, and comply with legal obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures to protect information. No method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is fully secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location, you may have rights to request access to, correction of, deletion of, or restriction of your personal information. You may also object to certain processing or request data portability where applicable.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Our services are not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us so we can review and remove it where appropriate.
  </p>

  <h2>International Use</h2>
  <p>
    If you access our services from outside the country where our infrastructure is located, your information may be transferred to and processed in other jurisdictions where data protection laws may differ.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the last updated date on this page. Continued use of the services after the update becomes effective constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or want to make a privacy-related request, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@borysonline.com">contact@borysonline.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalPageLayout>